Out of curiosity, I wrote a micro bench to compare the netty implementation and the old (but incorrect) implementation. 

It looks like the Netty implementation starts to become noticeably slower when the string is large, i.e. over 2048 characters, using roughly 20~30% more time. As long as correctness is concerned, I am +1 on the change. 

